WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.343
Benvenuto all'ultimo tutorial!

00:00:02.343 --> 00:00:05.029
Assicuriamoci che il disco non si

00:00:05.029 --> 00:00:06.373
esaurisca mai più.

00:00:06.373 --> 00:00:09.059
Faremo crescere un repository completo online,

00:00:09.059 --> 00:00:11.745
restituiremo al pool lo spazio eliminato

00:00:11.745 --> 00:00:14.431
e poi insegneremo alla macchina a

00:00:14.431 --> 00:00:17.118
fare entrambe le cose in automatico.

00:00:17.891 --> 00:00:19.112
Ecco il modello.

00:00:19.112 --> 00:00:21.960
Ogni repository è un file in un

00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:23.995
unico pool di datastore condiviso.

00:00:23.995 --> 00:00:26.843
I repository possono crescere online mentre i

00:00:26.843 --> 00:00:28.471
container continuano a girare.

00:00:28.471 --> 00:00:31.319
Ma eliminare dati all'interno di un repo

00:00:31.319 --> 00:00:33.353
non libera nulla da solo.

00:00:33.353 --> 00:00:36.202
Trim è ciò che restituisce i blocchi

00:00:36.202 --> 00:00:37.016
al pool.

00:00:37.016 --> 00:00:39.050
E una policy automatizza entrambi.

00:00:42.321 --> 00:00:45.125
Fill the repository most of the way and check:

00:00:45.125 --> 00:00:46.683
the filesystem is getting tight.

00:00:53.095 --> 00:00:53.931
Quasi pieno.

00:00:53.931 --> 00:00:55.603
È ora di crescere.

00:00:58.878 --> 00:01:00.179
Grow it online.

00:01:00.179 --> 00:01:02.781
The encrypted container and the filesystem

00:01:02.781 --> 00:01:05.382
expand while the containers keep running

00:01:05.382 --> 00:01:06.683
— zero downtime,

00:01:06.683 --> 00:01:07.551
zero unmount.

00:01:10.551 --> 00:01:11.872
Quattro gigabyte ora.

00:01:11.872 --> 00:01:13.633
Niente è stato riavviato.

00:01:16.911 --> 00:01:18.273
Verify from inside:

00:01:18.273 --> 00:01:19.181
same volume,

00:01:19.181 --> 00:01:20.542
double the room.

00:01:24.841 --> 00:01:26.800
L'app non se n'è mai accorta.

00:01:30.078 --> 00:01:31.386
Now the other direction.

00:01:31.386 --> 00:01:33.676
Delete the big file — but watch:

00:01:33.676 --> 00:01:36.292
the pool does not get the space back

00:01:36.292 --> 00:01:36.619
yet.

00:01:36.619 --> 00:01:38.908
Deleted blocks stay reserved inside the image.

00:01:40.658 --> 00:01:42.957
Liberato all'interno del repo,

00:01:42.957 --> 00:01:45.255
ancora di proprietà dell'immagine.

00:01:48.558 --> 00:01:51.140
Trim hands those blocks back to the datastore

00:01:51.140 --> 00:01:51.463
pool,

00:01:51.463 --> 00:01:51.785
online.

00:01:51.785 --> 00:01:54.044
This is the step most setups forget.

00:01:57.443 --> 00:01:57.895
Recuperato.

00:01:57.895 --> 00:02:00.604
Il pool può respirare di nuovo.

00:02:03.882 --> 00:02:06.053
Now stop doing this by hand.

00:02:06.053 --> 00:02:08.586
The policy enables automatic growth up to

00:02:08.586 --> 00:02:10.033
a ceiling you choose,

00:02:10.033 --> 00:02:11.118
plus scheduled trims.

00:02:17.699 --> 00:02:18.506
Policy salvata.

00:02:18.506 --> 00:02:21.330
La macchina prende il controllo da qui.

00:02:24.627 --> 00:02:25.688
Read it back:

00:02:25.688 --> 00:02:26.396
auto-grow on,

00:02:26.396 --> 00:02:27.810
ceiling at eight gigabytes,

00:02:27.810 --> 00:02:29.225
trim on a schedule.

00:02:33.764 --> 00:02:35.345
Impostato una volta,

00:02:35.345 --> 00:02:36.925
dimenticato in sicurezza.

00:02:40.218 --> 00:02:43.067
And the view that ties it

00:02:43.067 --> 00:02:43.542
together:

00:02:43.542 --> 00:02:46.390
storage health shows every repo's usage,

00:02:46.390 --> 00:02:47.340
the pool,

00:02:47.340 --> 00:02:50.188
and how much copy-on-write sharing is

00:02:50.188 --> 00:02:51.138
saving you.

00:02:51.138 --> 00:02:52.670
Una sola vista:

00:02:52.670 --> 00:02:53.181
utilizzo,

00:02:53.181 --> 00:02:55.735
risparmio e spazio per crescere.

00:02:56.515 --> 00:02:59.192
E con questo la serie è

00:02:59.192 --> 00:02:59.639
conclusa!

00:02:59.639 --> 00:03:00.531
Diciotto tutorial,

00:03:00.531 --> 00:03:02.762
dall'installazione allo storage in autopilota.

00:03:02.762 --> 00:03:05.439
I tuoi server sono di nuovo

00:03:05.439 --> 00:03:05.885
tuoi.

00:03:05.885 --> 00:03:07.670
Grazie per aver guardato!
